{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"e75f9712-9ab9-4cec-9888-9b232d1729f2","content":"To migrate an NUnit project from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform:\n\n1. **Update adapter** — replace `NUnit3TestAdapter` with `NUnitTestAdapter.MTP` (≥ 5.0):\n   ```xml\n   <PackageReference Include=\"NUnitTestAdapter.MTP\" Version=\"5.0.0\" />\n   ```\n\n2. **Remove** `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` — it's no longer needed.\n\n3. **Enable the platform** in your `.csproj`:\n   ```xml\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n   ```\n\n4. **Run tests** with `dotnet test` as before. You can also run the test executable directly (`./bin/Debug/net8.0/YourTests.exe`), since MTP produces a self-contained test host.\n\n5. **Optional extensions** — for code coverage, TRX output, etc., add the corresponding `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.*` packages (e.g., `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport`).\n\n> **Note:** The MTP adapter (`NUnitTestAdapter.MTP`) requires NUnit **4.x** (`NUnit` ≥ 4.0). If you're still on NUnit 3, you'll need to upgrade NUnit as well (mainly replacing `[TestFixture]` usage and updating any changed APIs).","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"36d207a2-3fe1-4db6-ae4b-3ab312490c56","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating an NUnit test project from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform. This is a knowledge question about .NET testing infrastructure, not a code change request. Let me provide a concise answer based on my knowledge.","outputTokens":419},"id":"fd2009a5-2c11-4357-b975-586c037475f5","timestamp":"2026-04-07T15:54:16.927Z","parentId":"65ee2585-73c9-42c0-ba98-842d4d624b0e"}
